column3: USA v. Phua et al - Criminal case; Paul Phua Trial Delayed Pending Ruling on FBI Tactics - Criminal case; Malaysia's Justice Minister Defends a Gangster - Macau trial.
column4: 2008 Royal Malaysia Police report on Phua was erroneous. Phua was not a member of the famed 14K Triad.
column5: The trial was postponed until the federal judge's ruling on whether the FBI improperly entered Las Vegas Strip hotel suites without a warrant before arresting and accusing a Malaysian businessman and his son of illegal Internet gambling. The defense attorneys wanted the evidence against the Phuas thrown out. The trial flagged off on Tuesday but none of the 15 defendants to the case, including Phua, turned up at the hearing. Lack of evidence hampers the trial.

column3: USA v. Phua et al.--criminal; Paul Phua Case Judge Discards FBI Evidence--ruling; Paul Phua Trial Delayed Pending Ruling on FBI Tactics--delayed; Malaysia’s Justice Minister Defends a Gangster--defense.
column5: Paul Phua's defense team called the ruling a “triumph for citizens everywhere,” and added that “law enforcement must not be reckless nor omit vital information when seeking a warrant.” Phua fought the Vegas case for a year and ultimately emerged practically free of all charges. The prosecutorial ineptitude was a big reason behind this.

column5: Paul Phua was permitted to leave on bail and take a flight to Las Vegas. He fought the Vegas case for a year and ultimately emerged practically free of all charges. The prosecutorial ineptitude was a big reason behind this. Phua can only hope that the Macau trial, i.e. being held at Court of First Instance will yield similar results.
